'''Edward Henry Clark''' (1870 – 24 June 1932) was an [[Independent politician|Independent]] [[Member of parliament|Member of Parliament]] for [[Port Chalmers (New Zealand electorate)|Chalmers]], in the [[South Island]] of New Zealand. He was a Member of the [[New Zealand Legislative Council|Legislative Council]] and for a time was its [[Chairman of Committees (New Zealand Legislative Council)|Chairman of Committees]].

==Early life==
Clark was born in [[Palmerston, New Zealand|Palmerston]], [[Otago]] and was a building contractor in [[Dunedin]].{{sfn|Hamer|1988 |p=362}}

==Political career==
