{{NZ parlbox footer}}
Edward Clark was on the council of Palmerston. He was [[Mayor]] 1904–1910 and 1919–1923.

Clark represented the {{NZ electorate link|Chalmers}} electorate in the [[New Zealand House of Representatives]] for six years from [[New Zealand general election, 1908|1908]] to 1914, when he retired.{{sfn|Wilson|1985|p=189}}

Clark was an Independent [[Liberalism|Liberal]] for all of his [[New Zealand Parliament|parliamentary]] career.{{sfn|Bassett|1982|p=66}}{{sfn|Wood|1996|p=88}}

Clark was a member of the Legislative Council from 25 June 1920 to his death in 1932.{{sfn|Wilson|1985|p=151}} He served as Chairman of Committees in 1931 and 1932.{{sfn|Wilson|1985|p=169}}

