{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox person | name = Sudhakar Tomar | image = Sudhakar tomar.jpg | caption = | native_name = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = India | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Entrepreneur | spouse = | children = }}
'''Sudhakar Tomar''' is a UAE-based, Indian entrepreneur, selected as one of the top 100 Indian leaders in the Arab World in 2016 and 2017 by [[Forbes]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url= http://arabic.arabianbusiness.com/business/2016/sep/20/422203|title=Arabian Business |date=September 2016 |accessdate=2018-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/en/list/the-top-indian-business-leaders-in-the-arab-world-2016-owners-/item/48/|title=The Top Indian Business Leaders By Forbes |date=2018-02-15 |accessdate=2018-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ml_Jid7exEsb |title= Sudhakar Tomar On BUDGET 2018 & Agriculture Sector| |date=Feb 2018 |accessdate=2018-02-28}}</ref>
He is the Managing Director at Hakan Agro DMCC, a multinational company in [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]]. He advocates farmer’s rights, stresses more on improving quality of food, food security and reducing malnutrition.
==Other roles==
He also serves as the board member of the CXO Alliance and ‘Dubai Food Trade Advisory Group of DMCC ([[Government of Dubai]]) and President at IMEA-TIIF - ‘India Middle East Agro Trade Investment and Investment Forum).<ref>{{cite web|author= |url= http://edition.pagesuite-professional.co.uk/launch.aspx?eid=a0359b0e-de21-49cf-9db2-a285a8d7ae5e&pnum=60 |title=Arabian Business |date=September 2016 |accessdate=2018-02-28}}</ref>
